## Purpose: Cursor as consumer

- **Primary consumer**: Cursor (and similar AI tools) will use the README as context when answering questions, generating code, or refactoring.
- **Goal**: Enable correct, project-consistent code by documenting structure, conventions, entry points, and where to look things up.
- **Principle**: Prefer **explicit over implicit**. Name files, paths, and patterns so the model can resolve references without guessing.
- **Complements**: A human-focused README can live in the same file; use clear section headers so both humans and Cursor can find what they need.

