## Project structure & file references

Use **explicit paths and roles** so Cursor can open or reference the right files.

- List directories and their purpose; call out files that are entry points or canonical examples.
- Use consistent path format: relative to repo root, e.g. `01_query_api/04_lab_query.py`, not `./04_lab_query.py` when describing the project.
- Reference other docs in the repo (e.g. `.cursor/rules/`, `docs/`) so Cursor knows where to find rules and specs.

Example:

```markdown
## Project structure

- `01_query_api/` — API query labs; start with [`03_mbta_api_test.py`](01_query_api/03_mbta_api_test.py) then [`04_lab_query.py`](01_query_api/04_lab_query.py).
- `06_agents/` — Ollama-based agents; run [`01_ollama.sh`](06_agents/01_ollama.sh) before Python/R scripts.
- `07_rag/` — RAG examples; data in `07_rag/data/`, entry scripts `02_txt.py` / `03_csv.py` / `04_sqlite.py`.
- `.cursor/rules/` — Project rules (coding style, README format, tools). Cursor applies these when editing matching files.
```

