## APIs and libraries

List external services and core libraries with **official doc links**. Cursor can use these to look up correct APIs and function signatures.

- **APIs**: Name the service and link to its API reference or getting-started page.
- **Libraries**: Name the library and link to docs (e.g. Requests, httr, ollama Python client).

Example:

```markdown
## APIs and libraries

- **MBTA API**: [MBTA V3 API](https://api-v3.mbta.com/docs/swagger/index.html); used in `01_query_api/`.
- **Ollama**: [Ollama API](https://github.com/ollama/ollama/blob/main/docs/api.md); Python usage in [`02_using_ollama.py`](06_agents/02_using_ollama.py).
- **Python HTTP**: [Requests](https://requests.readthedocs.io/en/latest/). **R HTTP**: [httr](https://httr.r-lib.org/).
```

