## Code examples & file references

Where helpful, include **short code snippets** that show project-specific usage, and **reference the real file** so Cursor can read full context.

- Prefer one canonical example per concept (e.g. "how we call the MBTA API in this project").
- Put the snippet in a fenced code block with language; below or above it, link to the file: e.g. "See [`01_query_api/04_lab_query.py`](01_query_api/04_lab_query.py) for the full script."
- For env or config, show the pattern without real keys.

Example:

```markdown
## Example: calling the API (Python)

This project uses a single module for the MBTA client and reads the key from the environment:

\`\`\`python
import os
import requests

API_KEY = os.environ.get("MBTA_API_KEY")
url = "https://api-v3.mbta.com/vehicles?filter[route]=1"
r = requests.get(url, headers={"x-api-key": API_KEY})
\`\`\`

Full script: [`01_query_api/04_lab_query.py`](01_query_api/04_lab_query.py). API reference: [MBTA V3 API](https://api-v3.mbta.com/docs/swagger/index.html).
```

