## Formatting for parseability

Use consistent structure so Cursor can locate sections reliably.

- **Headers**: One `#` for the document title; `##` for major sections; `###` for subsections. Use the same section names across READMEs when possible (e.g. "Project structure", "Tech stack", "APIs and libraries").
- **Lists**: Use bullets for options or roles; numbered lists for steps or sequence.
- **Paths**: Use repo-relative paths in links, e.g. `[04_lab_query.py](01_query_api/04_lab_query.py)`.
- **Code**: Fenced blocks with language tag; keep snippets short and point to the real file for full context.

