## Checklist for Cursor-oriented READMEs

When writing or updating a README for Cursor:

- [ ] Short project summary at the top.
- [ ] Project structure section with paths and roles of key dirs/files.
- [ ] Tech stack (languages, package managers, env/config needs).
- [ ] Entry points and run order when relevant.
- [ ] Conventions and pointer to `.cursor/rules/` or style docs.
- [ ] APIs and libraries with official doc links.
- [ ] At least one code example with a file reference; more for complex flows.
- [ ] Reference links section (table or list) for APIs and main libraries.
- [ ] Consistent `##` / `###` headers and repo-relative paths in links.
- [ ] No secrets; only env var names and config file names.

